Initial settings: Add a User, Network Settings, Configure Services, display the list of services which are running, Stop and turn OFF auto-start setting for a service if you donâ€™t need it, Sudo Settings

Add a User in kali linux
Cmd :- adduser username
Network Setting In Kali Linux
IP Address
Cmd:- sudo ifconfig -a
IP address and Netmask Network Configuration
Cmd:- sudo ifconfig eth0 192.168.1.10 netmask 255.255.255.0
Configure Services In Kali Linux
Cmd :- service ssh start
Cmd :- ssh username@hostname
Basic Command To Run , Enable , Start and Stop Services
Cmd :- systemctl [command] [service_name]
To stop and restart the service in Linux, use the command:
Cmd :- sudo systemctl restart SERVICE_NAME
Cmd :- sudo systemctl stop SERVICE_NAME
To Enable Services At Boot
Cmd :- sudo systemctl enable SERVICE_NAME
To display the list of services which are running In Kali Linux
Cmd :- sudo systemctl -t=service --state=running
Sudo settings
Cmd :- sudo apt install -y software_name
Any Command Which Are Used With Sudo Give A User A Super User Previliges.
